    "recap_headline": "Quinnipiac University",
    "recap_text": "Providence, Rhode Island \u2013\nThe Quinnipiac baseball program dropped its non-conference, midweek contest to the Brown Bears, 4-1. With the loss, the Bobcats fell to 4-9 early in the season.\nSCORE\nBrown 4, Quinnipiac 1\nRECORDS\nQuinnipiac (4-9) | Brown (4-6)\nWinning Pitcher \u2013 Christian Keel (1-0)\nLosing Pitcher \u2013\nJoseph Hiller\n(0-1)\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nThe Bobcats saw four straight batters reach base safely to start the game, and\nKyle Garbowski\ngot Quinnipiac on the board with an RBI single to right field.\nThe game would remain 1-0 Bobcats until the Bears tied it up in the fifth inning from a sacrifice fly to right field.\nIn the bottom half of the seventh inning, the Brown Bears struck for three runs to give them a 4-1 lead.\nThe Bobcats were held off the board after Brown took the lead as the Bears won the non-conference matchup on Tuesday.\nNEWS AND NOTES\nKyle Garbowski\nrecorded the only hit for the Bobcats in the game with his first-inning single.\nGarbowski leads the team with eleven RBIs this year.\nJacob Belecky\ngot the nod to start on the bump and went 3.0 innings, striking out three and allowing just two hits. Belecky only allowed two base runners in his three innings of work.\nMike Poncini\nand\nJ.C. Franconere\nboth pitched a scoreless inning in relief.\nON DECK\nThe Bobcats will open up MAAC play on Friday, March 13\nth\n, as they host the Sacred Heart Pioneers for the first game of a three-game series."
